**Maps and charts of the Iran crisis** 

Reuters does a fantastic work combining graphs and information about the current war in one single page. They constantly update it and it gives the readers a reliable place to get information from. 
The latest update is a graph showing the interrupted flights due to the Middle East conflict. It is so relevant to understand the impact of the conflict beyond just the "obvious." 
In this link you can also find survey from Feb. 28 to March 1 and asked 1,282 adults what they think of President Trump's use of military force. The speed in which they conducted the survey and added graphs to represent it is truly impressive and it gives a sense of what Americans are thinking. 
We can also find many other graphics in this link and it is a quick way to stay updated on the impact of the program.
As journalists, this is also a good example of where to compile date and how to present it in an easy-to-access way. They note their sources which I believe it to be helpful for those interested in fact checking. 

https://www.reuters.com/graphics/IRAN-CRISIS/MAPS/znpnmelervl/
